{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the ISAC-BS transmitted the dual-function signal for dual services in front of a potential eavesdropper using a simultaneous transmitting and reflecting IRS.",
    "The long-term secrecy rate was maximized subject to the eavesdropping SINR constraint, the communication QoS constraint, and the transmit power constraint by jointly optimizing the transmit beamforming, receive beamforming, as well as reflection and transmission coefficients at the IRS.",
    "Considering the time-varying wireless channels, they proposed two DRL-based algorithms to deal with the non-convex optimization problem.",
    "Rui et al. [250] proposed an RL-based anti-eavesdropping scheme for ISAC systems.",
    "Following the RL framework, the security of legitimate users can be improved by interacting with the eavesdropper."
  ]
}